<br>
That was... three years ago since I started. Hm... I still like it. A little. But I've also discovered, in my opinion, bigger and better things. Yu Yu Hakusho, Cowboy Bebop, Tenchi Muyo, Outlaw Star, Evangelion... *nods* I like the mangas of DB and DBZ. Mostly DB. That series is so cute and funny and... pervy. ^^;;<br>
<br>
Anyhoo! All I can say is... to each his own! Not everyone is gonna like what everyone else likes. people are different with different tastes. That simple. It has nothing to do with maturity. Just taste. Like, I don't care for Gundam (except I do love all those nice hot bishies! ^_^), but that's only because I like animes that have more, ah... interaction between the characters, rather than just interaction through big mechas containing characters. But that's just me! Other people love that show, and that's great. I have nothing against it.<br>
<br>
And one should definitely not hold anything against the creators. If someone can create a manga or anime that becomes popular and widespread with practically its own cult of adoring fans, more power to them! It should not be the creator who's blamed... but no one really should be blamed, either. If someone wants to copy an artist's style, well... that's their choice, and there ain't nothin' that can be done that I can see unless they do it on their own. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/ustealthmonkey0.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stealthmonkey0</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Pre-Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(5/19/02 7:37:27 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1592.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_cry.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: I'm gonna get alot of flack for this. DAMN DBZ!!!</span><hr size=1> I agree with you completely up until ercently all of the anime style art ive drawn was akira toriyama style<br>
